                                         CAPE TOWN - A murder case against a 14-year-old girl accused of stabbing to death a 15-year-old boy in George has been postponed until January.  The girl was arrested this week after she allegedly attacked and stabbed the boy in the chest during an argument.  The victim later died at a local clinic.  The police's Malcolm Poje said: “The matter was postponed to 5 January 2018 and she will be transferred to a juvenile hall detention centre in Cape Town till the next court appearance.”